to the editor although david a shaywitz op ed sept 19 emphasizes his uncle 's doctor 's dismissal of the possibility of additional months of life of a good quality what is even more distressing is that the patient 's wife sensed that the attending doctor was irritated when she called him at 4 am to report a high fever being awakened at such an hour is part of being a doctor and such irritation warrants censure by the chief of his department such supervision rarely exercised these days might have a chastening effect on many staff doctors who forget their professional oaths and responsibilities morton d bogdonoff md new york sept 19 2000 the writer is emeritus professor of medicine weill medical college of cornell university

